                                                                  2431 1451
The COMMARA-2.0 covariances in the fast neutron region were       2431 1451
adopted for ENDF/B-VII.1. These covariances used the ENDF/B-VI.8  2431 1451
evaluation as the starting point. The reason was that both the    2431 1451
basic files (adopted by ENDF/B-VII.0) and covariances were        2431 1451
produced by the highly experience ORNL group, Hetrick etal (1991) 2431 1451
We restored these covariances although CSEWG decided to drop them 2431 1451
from ENDF/B-VII.0. In case of Cr the justification for dropping   2431 1451
was relatively weak and mostly concerned the resonance region.    2431 1451
At inelastic scattering threshold region, the original            2431 1451
ENDF/B-VI.8 uncertainties were increased based on the dispersion  2431 1451
analysis of existing evaluations. Similarly, capture cross        2431 1451
sections uncertainties at high energies were increased to values  2431 1451
that were deemed to be more realistic.                            2431 1451
                                                                  2431 1451
An MF33 LB=5 section was added to the covariances for elastic     2431 1451
scattering at the upper end of the resonance region (0.5-1.43 MeV)2431 1451
to account for the uncertainty in the scattering radius R'. The   2431 1451
uncertainty in R' was taken from the Atlas of Neutron Resonances  2431 1451
and propagated to the elastic cross sections, using the 33-group  2431 1451
energy bins of the AFCI COMMARA-2.0 processed files. To account   2431 1451
for the capture uncertainty in COMMARA, an additional 5% MF33     2431 1451
LB=1 section was added from 100 keV - 1.43 MeV, where long-range  2431 1451
correlations are not fully accounted for in MF32 alone.           2431 1451
